OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FA speeding pleasure boat involved in a
OL,7,Ffatal crash in Portsmouth Harbour was
OL,8,Fbeing driven by a man who had drunk a
OL,9,Fsignificant amount of alcohol, an
OL,10,Finvestigation has found.
OL,12,FWilliam Blake, 61, and his friend,
OL,13,Fpassenger Gary Huntington, 60, died
OL,14,Fwhen the former's rigid inflatable
OL,15,Fboat, named Peaky Blinder, hit a
OL,16,Fstationary navigation beacon on August
OL,17,F14 last year.
OL,19,FAnother friend, aged 56, who was also
OL,20,Fa passenger, survived.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FThe Marine Accident Investigation
OL,7,FBranch (MAIB), which published a
OL,8,Freport into what happened, urged the
OL,9,Fgovernment to introduce legal alcohol
OL,10,Flimits for non-professional mariners
OL,11,Fsuch as Mr Blake.
OL,13,FNone of the trio - who were all thrown
OL,14,Finto the water by the impact - were
OL,15,Fwearing a life jacket, the MAIB said.
OL,17,FInvestigators found the Peaky Blinder
OL,18,Fwas driven at up to 49.7 knots
OL,19,F(57.1mph) in the harbour, almost five
OL,20,Ftimes the speed limit of 10 knots
OL,21,F(11.5mph).
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FAfter losing control, the boat struck
OL,7,Fthe beacon at 33.5 knots at 7.25pm.
OL,9,FThe friends were returning from a
OL,10,Fsocial trip to various locations in
OL,11,Fthe Solent and Isle of Wight area when
OL,12,Fthe accident happened.
OL,14,FThe report stated that "alcohol
OL,15,Fconsumption featured centrally
OL,16,Fthroughout the day", with the friends
OL,17,Fconsuming a glass of sparkling wine
OL,18,Feach before departure, about 10 cans
OL,19,Fof beer and cider between them at a
OL,20,Fhotel, and two rounds of drinks at a
OL,21,Frestaurant.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FMr Blake had a further one-and-a-half
OL,7,Fpints of beer and was "noticeably
OL,8,Funsteady on his feet", the MAIB said.
OL,10,FA toxicology report indicated there
OL,11,Fwas "a significant alcohol
OL,12,Fconcentration" in his blood, which had
OL,13,F"the potential to substantially impair
OL,14,Fhis judgement, reaction time and
OL,15,Fdecisionmaking", investigators added.
OL,17,FAfter being ejected overboard, the
OL,18,Fsurviving passenger saw Mr Blake
OL,19,Fbecome submerged and dived to try to
OL,20,Ffind him, but was unsuccessful.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FOn surfacing, they then swam to Mr
OL,7,FHuntington - who was floating
OL,8,Funconscious - pulled him towards the
OL,9,Fboat and held him alongside it.
OL,11,FAbout 20 minutes after the crash,
OL,12,Fresponding emergency services brought
OL,13,FMr Huntington out of the water and
OL,14,Fprovided first aid.
OL,16,FAfter being taken to shore he was
OL,17,Fairlifted to hospital, where he was
OL,18,Fdeclared dead.
OL,20,FMr Blake's body was found five days
OL,21,Fafter the crash.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
