OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FA post-mortem report gave his cause of
OL,7,Fdeath as drowning and a head injury.
OL,9,FThe report said there are "no
OL,10,Fenforceable alcohol limits for
OL,11,Fnonprofessional mariners", which it
OL,12,Fdescribed as a "longstanding
OL,13,Fregulatory gap".
OL,15,FIt made a series of safety
OL,16,Frecommendations, including that the
OL,17,Fsecretary of state for transport
OL,18,Fintroduces such limits.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FRob Loder, chief inspector of marine
OL,7,Faccidents, said: "It is well
OL,8,Funderstood that consumption of alcohol
OL,9,Fresults in an elevated risk of having
OL,10,Fan accident.
OL,12,F"The introduction of alcohol limits
OL,13,Ffor recreational boaters has been the
OL,14,Fsubject of previous MAIB
OL,15,Frecommendations.
OL,17,F"It is to be hoped that action will
OL,18,Fnow be taken, such that fatal
OL,19,Faccidents in which excessive alcohol
OL,20,Fconsumption is a contributing factor
OL,21,Fbecome a thing of the past."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,FRichard Ballantyne, chief executive of
OL,7,Findustry body the British Ports
OL,8,FAssociation, said Parliament provided
OL,9,Fthe powers to address the lack of an
OL,10,Falcohol limit in 2003.
OL,12,FHe went on: "Twenty-three years later,
OL,13,Fthe relevant provisions have still not
OL,14,Fbeen brought into force, despite
OL,15,Frepeated warnings from ports, harbour
OL,16,Fmasters and safety investigators.
OL,18,F"The government should accept the
OL,19,FMAIB's recommendations and publish a
OL,20,Fclear timetable for implementing them.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,390,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1784281689
OL,3,CSpeeding boat in fatal crash was
OL,4,Cdriven by drunk man, investigators find
OL,6,F"The evidence has been under review
OL,7,Ffor long enough. We should not wait
OL,8,Ffor another fatal accident before
OL,9,Fclosing a loophole that should never
OL,10,Fhave remained open."
OL,12,FA Department for Transport (DfT)
OL,13,Fspokesperson said: "This was a tragic
OL,14,Fincident, and our thoughts remain with
OL,15,Fthe families and friends of William
OL,16,FBlake and Gary Huntington.
OL,18,F"Safety is our number one priority,
OL,19,Fand we take the findings and
OL,20,Frecommendations of this report very
OL,21,Fseriously.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
